## The "Miss the Old Look?" Button

This is a great idea. Here's the cleanest implementation approach:

**Option A (easiest):** A floating button pinned to the corner of every page:
```
┌─────────────────────────────┐
│  📺  Miss the old look?     │
└─────────────────────────────┘
```
Clicking it stores a cookie/localStorage flag and redirects to archived copies of the original pages (name them `index-classic.html`, `homepage-classic.html`, etc.). The classic pages get the same button in reverse: *"See the new look →"*

**Option B (fancier):** A toggle in the splash/index page like a checkbox styled as a retro flip switch: *"Classic Mode: [ON/OFF]"* — this sets a flag in localStorage and all pages read it to apply either the new or old stylesheet.

**Recommended:** Option B — it's more polished and fits the OS vibe perfectly. Display it as a dialog box popup: `[ ] Enable Classic Mode` with Win95 radio buttons.

